snippet.textDisplay: Y'all usually I really don't say anything, but on this I have to speak! I personally rooted for the Dancing Dolls from the gate! But what y'all did to Miss D was very disrespectful! Only three of the members volunteered to for the solo for a liturgical dance theme! And one of the members was one of the veterans. To be brutally honest. I was highly disappointed in y'all simply because nobody else stepped up! I bet you if it was a Beyonce dance theme every last one of y'all hands would have been raised on up. But if it have to do with the one who gave you the talent and the gifts in the first place. Don't nobody wanted to raise y'all hands! That ain't right y'all! That ain't right! Ms. D girl I felt  your pain and your anger with the girls and I was livid with you! I was like oh I'm gonna shut it down! But the Lord Jesus had other plans. He was like Violet calm down and keep watching! I'm gonna say this to y'all! Don't you ever refuse to do anything for the Lord Jesus simply because you really don't know what blessings and opportunities that God Almighty Himself has in store for every last one of y'all! Make it be the first and the last time y'all pull that stunt ever again in life! To Ms. D I felt your pain and your anger. And I really don't blame you for walking out! I would've had done the same exact thing and worse! For real talk right there! Of all the creative dances that you've done Ms. D this one by far was the best! When the girls was done with the dance. I was praising God! Speaking in my Heavenly language! I was moved to tears! Y'all I was done because I was not going to watch the show no more! But God used the girls and Ms. D to encourage me to keep on watching! This was past getting a trophy! We're talking about the Creator of the universe. VK.
